* Profiles

** compile-izpack

  To package the installer Jar for the <<<project-install>>>, Maven must be
called with the <<<package>>> goal and with the <<<compile-izpack>>> profile
active. Two Jar files will be created after the successfully packaging, the
<<<project-install-VERSION-single-jar.jar>>>, which is the executable Jar file
of the project that contains all the dependencies,
and <<<project-install-VERSION.jar>>>, which is the installer Jar. The
placeholder <<<VERSION>>> is replaced by the project's version string.

---
project-install/ $ mvn package -P compile-izpack
---

** make-install-exe

  To package the installer Windows executable for the <<<project-install>>>,
Maven must be called with the <<<package>>> goal and
with the <<<make-install-exe>>> profile active. The installer Jar
from the <<<compile-izpack>>>
profile <<<project-install-VERSION.jar>>> must exists in the target directory.
After the goal successfully finished, the
file <<<project-install-VERSION.exe>>> is created. The
placeholder <<<VERSION>>> is replaced by the project's version string.

---
project-install/ $ mvn package -P make-install-exe
---

** make-exe

  To package the application Windows executable for the <<<project-install>>>,
Maven must be called with the <<<package>>> goal and
with the <<<make-exe>>> profile active. The bundled Jar
from the <<<compile-izpack>>>
profile <<<project-install-VERSION-single-jar.jar>>> must exists in the
target directory. After the goal successfully finished, the
file <<<project-install-VERSION-single-jar.exe>>> is created. The
placeholder <<<VERSION>>> is replaced by the project's version string.

---
project-install/ $ mvn package -P make-exe
---

